{
    "Body": " Savvy is a cutting-edge cryptocurrency platform working towards the creation of a global toolkit for crypto-based financial products. With the initial version of our payment gateway already up and running, we\u2019re now focused on incorporating new products into our growing ecosystem. However, our work is not yet complete! We\u2019re in need of a Communications expert to apply their impressive skills towards the creation of even more amazing products at Savvy. Requirements We\u2019re looking for a comms all-rounder who can write and manage our content, communications and public relations. You\u2019ll have knowledge on the latest trends and have the ability to work across multiple platforms including; blogs, press releases, social media, keynotes and general marketing. When you are onboarded, we\u2019ll expect you to: - You have a knack for writing company blurb, news, product content, updating company blogs and social posts. - You are an ideas person, finding interesting topics to cover, headlines and story ideas. - You have a way with words, a natural writer who can conjure up themes and shape a story that can play through our blog, PR, keynotes and general marketing. - You will be shaping the content of the business, working directly with the CMO and Product Managers to clearly articulate the key value proposition of our products for the audience. - You are adept at taking a product from conception to the development and implementation of marketing collateral. - While you love to develop content, you are no stranger to proactively approaching and working directly with reporters to spar up a story or manage crisis communications. - You are keen on tracking success and measuring the results. It\u2019s great but not required if you have: - 8+ years of experience in communications with experience working with teams and agencies. - Experience working in companies of different sizes ideally in technology and startups. - Someone who likes to be in the know of the latest trends. - You are keen to learn about blockchain and cryptocurrency and drive straight in! Why work with us? - Highly competitive day rate depending on experience - Fast-paced, remote start-up environment Possibility to make a big impact on the product - Location: Home Office / Fully Remote - Start date: ASAP Skills Blockchain, crypto, marketing Compensation Competitive Hourly Rate Applications for this job are currently closed. ", 
